Joined at the hip: Jubilee and ODM NDC posters. [Courtesy]  ODM and Jubilee parties are holding their National Delegates Conventions at Kasarani and KICC, respectively on a Saturday expected to be Raila Odinga's defining moment under Azimio la Umoja movement.  President Uhuru Kenyatta arrives for the Jubilee NDC at the KICC, Nairobi. [PSCU]  The movement that brings together over 10 political parties in support of Odinga’s presidency is set to join ranks with President Uhuru Kenyatta’s Jubilee in March during a joint session where the two parties will formally form Azimio la Umoja coalition.  ODM leader Raila Odinga at Kasarani during ODM's convention. [Samson Wire, Standard] At today’s conventions, thousands of delegates and allied leaders started streaming into the venues as early as 6am in support of their respective parties in a show of might against Deputy William Ruto, who has himself joined forces with ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya's Moses QWetang'ula to form Kenya Kwanza Alliance.  President Uhuru Kenyatta at the KICC during the Jubilee Party NDC at Kasarani. [Standard]  Below are some photos from the NDCs;   Jubilee delegates at the KICC, Nairobi. [PSCU]  A section of Jubilee Party delegates at the KICC, Nairobi. [PSCU]  A section of Jubilee delegates. [Courtesy]  Esther Passaris, Millicent Okatch and Senator Agnes Zani at Kasarani. [Twitter, @EstherPassaris]  Kanu Chairman Gideon Moi (R) arrives at KICC for the Jubilee Party NDC. [Twitter, @ItsNyambane]  Businessman Suleiman Shahbal and COTU secretary-general Francis Atwoli at Kasarani. [Twitter, @SuleimanShahbal]  Businesman Suleiman Shahbal with Francis Ole Kaparo at Kasarani. [Twitter, @SuleimanShahbal]  A section of ODM leaders and delegates at Kasarani. [Twitter, @agnes_zani]     By Betty Njeru | 1 hour ago By Too Jared | 1 hour ago By Dennis Tarus | 3 hours ago By Fred Kagonye | 3 hours ago